                            <comment id="12324464" author="army" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2005 03:38:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch that creates the following suites for testing Derby&apos;s XML datatype and operators:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;xmlTests:  run XML tests against Derby embedded&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;xmlTestsNet:  run XML tests against Derby Network Server with JCC&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;xmlTestsNetClient: run XML tests against Derby Network Server with Derby Client&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;xmlSuite: run all of the above suites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There are currently only two XML tests (lang/xml_general.sql and lang/xmlBinding.java); when more are added they should be added to the xmlTests.runall file and then they will be included in all other suites automatically.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE: in order to run any of the XML tests, one must have Xerces in the classpath.  For that reason, the XML tests are NOT included in &quot;derbyall&quot; at this time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If anyone has time to review and/or commit, I&apos;d be grateful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12324489" author="fuzzylogic" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2005 07:46:08 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk with revision 280680.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12329308" author="army" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2005 01:33:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for committing, Andrew.  I verified that the XML tests/suites work after the patch was committed, so I am closing this issue.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE: depending on the version of JVM that people are using, attempts to run these XML tests could potentially fail with a &quot;java.lang.IllegalAccessError&quot; or the message &quot;Could not load the property file &apos;output_xml.properties&quot;.  This is &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; a problem with Derby nor with the XML tests; rather, it is a known issue for some JDK releases.  For more, see: &lt;a href=&quot;http://xml.apache.org/xalan-j/faq.html#faq-N1033F&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://xml.apache.org/xalan-j/faq.html#faq-N1033F&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
